<article> <h1>The Sawyer family</h1> <p>The Sawyer live at 87 King Street.</p> <br> <p>In the morning, Mr. Sawyer goes to work and the children go to school.</p> <p>Mrs. Sawyer stays at home every day. She does the 【housework】.</p> <br> <p>She always eats her lunch at noon.</p> <br> <p>In the afternoon, she usually sees her friends. They often drink tea 【together】.</p> <p>In the evening, the children come home from school. They arrive home early.</p> <p>Mr. Sawyer comes home from work. He arrives home late.</p> <br> <p>At night, the children always do their 【homework】. Then they go to bed. Mr. Sawyer usually reads his newspaper, but                 sometimes he and his wife watch television.</p> </article> <section> <section> <h4>housework</h4> <dl> <dt>n.[U] 家务劳动；家务事|the work involved in taking care of a home and family, for example cleaning and cooking</dt> <dd>to do the housework|做家务</dd> </dl> </section> <section> <h4>together</h4> <dl> <dt>adv.在一起；共同|with or near to sb/sth else; with each other</dt> <dd>We grew up together.|我们是在一块儿长大的。</dd> <dd>Together they climbed the dark stairs.|他们一起登上黑洞洞的楼梯。</dd> <dd>Get all the ingredients together before you start cooking.|把所有的材料放在一起再开始烹饪。</dd> <dd>Stay close together ─I don't want anyone to get lost.|紧紧靠在一起，我不想把谁给丢了。</dd> </dl> </section> <section> <h4>homework</h4> <dl> <dt>n.（学生的）家庭作业|work that is given by teachers for students to do at home</dt> <dd>I still haven't done my geography homework.|我还没做完地理科家庭作业呢。</dd> <dd>How much homework do you get?|你有多少家庭作业？</dd> <dd>I have to write up the notes for homework.|我不得不详细地写好家庭作业笔记。</dd> </dl> </section> </section>	</template>